# Chart the JoelClaw Voice Workroom

## Finish line

A joelclaw voice agent Joel can phone that answers reliably, reads the wiki, and runs conversational grilling and planning as durable workroom sessions — bound to the same pi session and Discord thread, resumable as voice or text, recallable through the existing memory pipeline, and discoverable across every product's brief.

The first proof is dial tone with fail-loud canaries plus wiki and recall tools on a real call; the map is done when the workroom binding and grill-master split are decided and the phase-2 build is specifiable.

## Notes

### Product boundary

- This is an agent **for Joel**, not for the system: it acts with his user session, tools, and memory. Caller allowlist stays fail-closed.
- Phone-first. Browser WebRTC and Tesla/private-audio surfaces come later (the wiki map's "Research Phone, Tesla, and Private Audio Delivery" ticket adjoins this effort).
- Conversational grilling and planning is the core job. Deep work is enqueued to the engine and continues after hangup; results land in the bound Discord thread.
- Voice may write to trackers (append decisions, create/claim/resolve tickets) and kick off jobs and research. It never edits code or runs arbitrary commands. This supersedes `roles/voice.md` — the ADR ticket records it.

### Fixed technical direction (decided in the 2026-07-11 design session)

- **Media plane: LiveKit Cloud** (SFU + SIP). Telnyx DID repoints from the dead k8s SIP path to a LiveKit Cloud trunk + dispatch rule. The worker on flagg connects outbound over WSS — zero inbound exposure. Self-hosted media on k8s never returns.
- **Worker:** extend the existing Python LiveKit Agents worker (`infra/voice-agent/main.py` — Deepgram STT, ElevenLabs TTS, Silero VAD). Runs as Joel-user LaunchAgent (`com.joel.voice-agent`); Central system-daemon migration is deferred until the tool-auth story (gog keyring, `~/.joelclaw` paths) is untangled.
- **LLM:** OpenRouter is explicitly approved for the voice loop (exception to the repo-wide ban; the ADR ticket records it). Pipeline STT→LLM→TTS first; swap to a speech-to-speech realtime model only if median turn latency still annoys after a week of real calls.
- **Two-tier loop:** the fast conversational loop holds the call and runs cheap tools directly; the pi-discord-threads engine handles deep runs. Exact grilling split is the open grill-master ticket.
- **State layers:** pi session JSONL is conversation truth; the grill-master tracker (`.svx` in each product's `.brain`) is effort truth; Typesense (`voice_transcripts` + `joelclaw recall`) is recall. **No Qdrant** — recall migrated to Typesense; remaining Qdrant mentions in `main.py` are stale docstrings.
- **Engine seam:** extend pi-discord-threads in place (registry, `PiRuntimePort`, steer/followUp, `PromptProgress`). Keep the voice worker's engine client behind a thin interface; `@ai-sdk/harness-pi` is watch-and-converge only — today it lacks resume and steer and is Vercel-Sandbox-shaped.
- **Memory:** voice turns feed the observation pipeline (compacted/starred/ranked, short- and long-term, Typesense → markdown) via the existing `voice/call.completed` → `memory/session.ended` path. Compacted turns in the session JSONL; verbatim transcript in `voice_transcripts`, cross-referenced.
- **Durability posture — silent drift is the enemy** (ADR-0178's failure was "ringing with no answer"; the NAS incident proved live ≠ boot-durable):
  - Missed-call paging via Telnyx webhooks; worker-registration cron canary; daily synthetic end-to-end call.
  - Answering depends only on LiveKit + the LLM key; every tool fails soft.
  - Per-turn persistence during the call, not save-at-close. Post-call processing is Inngest at-least-once, idempotency-keyed by call ID.
  - `verify-voice.sh` hard-fails on missing plist, unregistered worker, unleasable secrets; runs at boot and on cron.
- **Wiki access phase 1:** static edition endpoints (`http://127.0.0.1:8790/latest.json`, `data/editions/<date>.json`) plus `joelclaw recall`. No new search index until edition + recall proves insufficient.

### Execution override

This effort carries phase-0/phase-1 execution into the map (dial tone, canaries, voice tools, grill-master CLI): those tasks unblock the remaining decisions — the grill-master split needs real calls to measure, and the workroom binding needs the CLI's contract to bind to.

### Sources every session should consult

- `/skill:grill-master`
- `/skill:brain-first-workflow`
- `/skill:grill-me` and `/skill:grill-with-docs`
- `/skill:effect-ts`
- `/skill:session-search`
- `/skill:tailnet-topology` for any URL or exposure question
- `/skill:panda-host` for the panda recovery ticket

Provenance: this map was charted from the 2026-07-11 flagg design session (Claude, voice-workroom architecture). Load-bearing prior art: `infra/voice-agent/main.py` (the shipped ADR-0043 worker), pi-discord-threads `src/engine/**` + `src/registry.ts` + `src/pi-runtime.ts` (the transport-agnostic core), `packages/system-bus/src/inngest/functions/voice-call-completed.ts`, `packages/system-bus/src/lib/typesense.ts`.

## Decision ledger

<!-- Closed ticket resolutions are appended here as one-line linked gists. -->

- [Restore Dial Tone via LiveKit Cloud](./restore-dial-tone-via-livekit-cloud.svx) — live both directions on new DID +1 360 389 4321; old number was lost to a lapsed Telnyx balance, LiveKit SIP URIs must come from the dashboard (wildcard DNS makes guesses resolve-then-404), and the worker now judges callers by SIP participant attribute after waiting for the phone leg to join.
- [Build Fail-Loud Canaries and Boot Verification](./build-fail-loud-canaries.svx) — killing the worker paged Joel in 4m05s (proven live): a 5-min registration canary (bare room-create probe — automatic dispatch makes the worker join in ~2s, no phone needed), daily synthetic self-call (answered in 3s; worker speaks a token to its own DID), 6-hourly balance monitor, missed-call detector behind a new `telnyx` webhook provider (Telnyx confirmed delivering FQDN call events; dark until the portal public key lands in agent-secrets as `telnyx_public_key`), and `verify-voice.sh` (21 probes) at boot + every 30 min. Pages go out via Telnyx call+SMS *and* gateway urgent so a dead Telnyx account can't silence its own alarm. Surfaced [Add Graceful Drain to Voice Worker Restarts](./add-graceful-drain-voice-worker.svx).

## Not yet specified

- The registry multi-surface surgery spec — how `ThreadRecord` becomes a transport-neutral workroom/surface store — waits on the grill-master and workroom-binding decisions.
- Progress narration UX for engine runs over voice: how `PromptProgress` frames become speech without babbling.
- Central system-daemon migration of the worker (boot-without-login) once tool auth is untangled.
- Browser WebRTC "talk to joelclaw" surface on the wiki (free with LiveKit Cloud, unscoped).
- Speech-to-speech model swap, if the latency trigger fires.
- Wayfinder-over-voice on products whose tracker is GitHub or Linear rather than local-brain.
- How starring/ranking of voice-derived observations is reviewed by a human.

## Out of scope

- Self-hosted SFU/SIP on k8s, or any return to the Talos/Colima cluster for the voice path.
- Voice editing code or running arbitrary commands — write scopes stop at trackers and job kickoff.
- Public or multi-caller phone access beyond the fail-closed allowlist.
- Replacing the Discord surface — voice is additive; text remains first-class.
- A wiki semantic-search index in phase 1.
- Podcast/edition audio generation — that belongs to the wiki map's audio ticket, not this effort.
